elements.content: Where did you grow up

resource.alt: A woman checking her clothes fit in front of a mirror
Free stock photo of a woman sitting on a chair with a dog

elements.content: It feels like Travis, 30, has always been famous — an indelible screen presence and iconic parents will do that.
That was what I liked growing up. And also, that was what I thought I was suited for. I didn’t see a lot of people who looked like me in big movies.

resource.alt: People walking on bridge during daytime
Free stock photo of a woman reading newspaper

elements.content: There is so much diverse energy in Brooklyn. You can take a turn down a lovely neighborhood street, or get that lively nightlife if you want.
A lot of what inspires me is rooted in Brooklyn. I love to be at home whenever I can and I really fill my place with treasures from people near and dear to me.
